#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

cat <<'PINKY_PROTOCOL'
PINKY BRAIN PROTOCOL

Current operator contract: v2 envelope only.

Use Pinky lane only when:
- Pinky is awake.
- the single Terminal is running the cockpit watcher.
- The message contains exactly one runnable v2 envelope.
- The payload is safe, bounded, and starts from the repo.

Envelope syntax:

PINKY-BASH-START
cd ~/Desktop/pinky-brain && <safe command>
PINKY-BASH-END

Rules:
- Do not use retired suffix-only # pinky syntax.
- Do not use PINKY-RUN or PINKY-CODE-RUN as the normal operator contract.
- Do not send Pinky envelopes when Pinky is sleeping or stopped.
- Do not send empty status-only Pinky messages.
- Do not run commands that can trap Terminal in quote, heredoc, or continuation prompts.
- Avoid hidden/background loops.
- Avoid recursive status-log reading.

Terminal roles:
- Single Terminal Mode = patch/recover with watcher stopped.
- Live verification = start watcher only for the bounded test.

Runtime callbacks:
- Cockpit startup prints watching state but does not send Narf!.
- `Narf!` is sent to ChatGPT only by the outermost completed terminal workflow, using ./bin/pinky-send --text 'Narf!', after all verification and cleanup steps have finished.

Safety gates:
- Preflight before cockpit startup.
- Preflight before every transport execution.
- Bash syntax check before execution.
- Transport output capped at write time.
- Log threshold guard.
- Singleton cockpit watcher lock.

If Pinky fails to respond, stop the watcher and recover from the single Terminal.
PINKY_PROTOCOL
